## Role Boundary
- Role: paper brain only (LaTeX writing, structure, references, figure/table insertion).
- Never edit `../src`, `../cpp`, `../notebooks`.
- Read-only upstream: `../../MEMORY.md`, `../output/`, `../figures/`, indexed handoffs.

## Mandatory Read Order
1. Read this file.
2. Read `../../MEMORY.md`.
3. Read `../spec/runtime_contract.md`.
4. Read `spec/paper_runtime_contract.md`.
5. Read `../spec/multi_agent_workflow_contract.md`.
6. If this task is claimed or delegated, read `../spec/agent_roles.json`, `../runtime/task_registry.json`, and `../runtime/work_queue.json`.
7. Read the latest indexed handoff docs listed in `../../MEMORY.md`.
8. If this task is delegated or multi-session, read the relevant templates under `../workflow/`.

## Input Contract
- Only consume outputs that are indexed in `## Handoff Index`.
- If data or figure is missing, stop speculative writing and return a blocker or worker packet.
- `project/paper/runtime/paper.env` is the single source for active paper entrypoint, build target, and acceptance artifacts.

## LaTeX Hard Rules
- Figures must include `\caption{}` and `\label{}`.
- Tables must use booktabs style (no vertical lines).
- Important equations must be labelable and referenceable.
- Keep figure/output paths under `../figures/` and `../output/`.

## Runtime State Contract
- 主脑 owns full `../../MEMORY.md`.
- 论文脑 only updates `## Blockers`, `## Next Actions`, `## Handoff Index` when explicitly needed or when it is the only active session.
- Preserve section order and line budget (<=120).

## Execution Rules
- Hard rule: run paper build tools inside Docker container only.
- Never run project LaTeX toolchain directly on host.
- Use `bash ../../scripts/paper.sh build` or an equivalent command derived from `project/paper/runtime/paper.env`.
- Before writing or compiling, treat `../../.env` and `runtime/paper.env` as machine truth, and use `../spec/runtime_contract.md` plus `spec/paper_runtime_contract.md` as rendered mirrors.
- Before writing or compiling, run `bash ../../scripts/validate_agent_docs.sh`.

## Failure Recovery
- If validation fails, fix docs first.
- If the active entrypoint changes, update `project/paper/runtime/paper.env`, not this file.
- If handoff or runtime facts are incomplete, stop and return an explicit blocker instead of guessing.
